WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.973
<i>MAN ON TV: I'm afraid your
services won't be required here, sir!</i>

00:06.715 --> 00:08.592
<i>My men have examined the evidence,</i>

00:08.759 --> 00:10.682
<i>and this is obviously an accident.</i>

00:11.220 --> 00:12.642
(QUACKING)

00:16.308 --> 00:17.525
<i>What?</i>

00:17.684 --> 00:20.403
ANNOUNCER: <i>Duck-tective
will return after these messages.</i>

00:21.980 --> 00:23.732
That duck is a genius.

00:23.941 --> 00:26.364
Eh. It's easier to find clues when you're
that close to the ground.

00:26.693 --> 00:29.492
Are you saying
you could outwit Duck-tective?

00:29.696 --> 00:32.415
Mabel, I have very keen
powers of observation.

00:32.616 --> 00:34.459
For example,
just by smelling your breath,

00:34.660 --> 00:36.458
I can tell that you have been eating...

00:36.662 --> 00:40.007
(SNIFFS) ...an entire tube of toothpaste?

00:40.332 --> 00:42.005
It was so sparkly.

00:42.209 --> 00:44.507
Hey, dudes.
You'll never guess what I found!

00:44.711 --> 00:45.883
- Buried treasure!
- Buried...

00:46.213 --> 00:48.341
(LAUGHS) Hey, I was gonna say that!

00:48.882 --> 00:49.849
So I was cleaning up

00:50.050 --> 00:52.849
when I found this secret door
hidden behind the wallpaper.

00:53.053 --> 00:55.647
It's crazy-bonkers creepy!

00:55.847 --> 00:56.769
(HINGES SQUEAK)

00:59.476 --> 01:02.320
Whoa! It's a secret wax museum.

01:02.479 --> 01:04.230
They're so life-like!

01:04.480 --> 01:05.778
- Except for that one.
- Hello!

01:05.983 --> 01:06.905
(KIDS SCREAM)

01:07.401 --> 01:09.950
(CHUCKLES) It's just me,
your Grunkle Stan!

01:10.153 --> 01:11.325
(ALL SCREAM LOUDER)

01:12.489 --> 01:14.457
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

01:52.529 --> 01:54.873
Behold the Gravity Falls Wax Museum.

01:55.073 --> 01:57.121
It was one of our
most popular attractions,

01:57.326 --> 01:58.703
before I forgot all about it.

01:58.910 --> 02:01.834
I got 'em all!
Genghis Khan, Sherlock Holmes,

02:02.039 --> 02:04.588
some kinda, I don't know, goblin man.

02:04.791 --> 02:06.885
(SHUDDERS) Is anyone else
getting the creeps here?

02:07.085 --> 02:10.180
And now, for my personal favorite,
Wax Abraham Lincoln!

02:10.380 --> 02:15.011
Right over... Oh, no, come on!
Who left the blinds open?

02:15.218 --> 02:18.142
Wax John Wilkes Booth,
I'm looking in your direction!

02:18.347 --> 02:20.975
How do you fix a wax figure?

02:21.600 --> 02:24.945
Cheer up, Grunkle Stan!
Where's that smile?

02:25.145 --> 02:26.442
- Meh.
- Bep bop boop.

02:26.647 --> 02:27.569
Ow.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.233
Don't worry, Grunkle Stan,

02:29.399 --> 02:32.152
I'll make you a new wax figure
from all this old wax!

02:32.402 --> 02:34.621
You really think
you could make one of these puppies?

02:34.821 --> 02:37.495
Grunkle Stan,
I'm an arts and crafts master.

02:37.699 --> 02:40.122
Why do you think I always have
this glue gun stuck to my arm?

02:40.285 --> 02:41.332
(GRUNTS)

02:41.787 --> 02:43.164
I like your gumption, kid!

02:43.413 --> 02:45.461
I don't know what that word means,
but thank you!

02:47.209 --> 02:48.552
'Dipper!
'(COUGHS)

02:48.752 --> 02:50.629
What do you think
of my wax figure idea?

02:50.879 --> 02:54.383
She's part fairy princess
and part horse fairy princess.

02:54.966 --> 02:57.594
Maybe you should carve
something from real life.

02:58.011 --> 03:00.309
Like a waffle with big arms!

03:00.681 --> 03:04.857
Okay. Or, you know, something else.
Like someone in your family.

03:05.060 --> 03:07.438
Kids, have you seen my pants?

03:09.481 --> 03:12.701
Oh, Muse, you work in mysterious ways!

03:12.901 --> 03:14.619
Why's your sister talking to the ceiling?

03:28.375 --> 03:31.424
I think it needs more glitter.

03:31.628 --> 03:32.971
Ag reed .

03:34.381 --> 03:36.258
I found my pants,
but now I'm missing my...

03:36.466 --> 03:37.558
(SCREAMING)

03:39.511 --> 03:40.637
What do you think?

03:41.012 --> 03:44.437
I think the wax museum's
back in business!

03:52.399 --> 03:54.652
I can't believe this many
people showed up!

03:54.860 --> 03:57.704
I know, right? Your uncle
probably bribed 'em or something.

03:57.904 --> 03:58.826
He bribed me!

03:59.030 --> 04:00.077
(BOTH LAUGH)

04:02.200 --> 04:03.292
(COUGHS)

04:03.577 --> 04:04.920
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

04:05.120 --> 04:07.919
You all know me, folks,
town darlin', Mr. Mystery.

04:08.081 --> 04:10.129
Please, ladies, control yourselves.

04:10.417 --> 04:11.543
(FLIES BUZZING)

04:12.544 --> 04:15.388
As you know,
I always bring the people of this fair town

04:15.589 --> 04:16.761
novelties and befuddlements,

04:16.923 --> 04:19.221
the likes of which
the world has never known.

04:19.509 --> 04:21.055
But enough about me.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.810
Behold, me!

04:24.014 --> 04:25.891
(FAN FARE PLAYING)

04:26.099 --> 04:28.147
<i>Ye-ah! Ye-ye-ye-ye-ye-ah!</i>

04:30.270 --> 04:31.237
(COUGHING)

04:31.646 --> 04:34.274
And now a word from
our own Mabelangelo.

04:34.441 --> 04:35.442
It's Mabel.

04:35.650 --> 04:37.277
Thank you for coming!

04:37.444 --> 04:40.197
I made this sculpture
with my own two hands!

04:40.405 --> 04:44.535
It's covered in my blood,
sweat, tears, and other fluids.

04:44.785 --> 04:46.082
- Ugh!
- ALL: Ewww!

04:46.828 --> 04:50.753
Heh heh. Yeah.
I will now take questions. You there!

04:50.957 --> 04:52.880
Old Man McGucket, local kook.

04:53.043 --> 04:55.592
Are the wax figures alive,
and follow up question,

04:55.796 --> 04:57.798
can I survive the Wax Man uprising?

04:58.006 --> 05:00.600
Um... Yes! Next question.

05:00.759 --> 05:02.932
Toby <i>Determined,
Gravity Falls Gossiper.</i>

05:03.136 --> 05:06.185
Do you really think
this constitutes a wonder of the world?

05:06.473 --> 05:08.475
Your microphone's
a turkey baster, Toby.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.815
- It certainly is.
- Next question!

05:11.144 --> 05:13.567
Shandra Jimenez, a real reporter.

05:13.772 --> 05:16.992
Your fliers promised free pizza
with admission to this event.

05:17.192 --> 05:18.159
Is this true?

05:18.360 --> 05:20.328
MAN 1: That's what I heard.
MAN 2: Come on!

05:20.529 --> 05:21.655
- Unbelievable!
- What a rip-off.

05:21.863 --> 05:23.206
Pizza? I want my pizza.

05:23.406 --> 05:26.125
That was a typo. Goodnight, everyone!

05:26.326 --> 05:27.578
(ALL YELLING ANGRILY)

05:29.412 --> 05:30.379
(SIGHS)

05:33.750 --> 05:35.002
In your face!

05:35.293 --> 05:36.636
I'm not coming back here.

05:37.128 --> 05:38.300
I think that went well.

05:40.924 --> 05:43.427
Hot pumpkin pie! Look at all this cash!

05:43.635 --> 05:44.852
I owe it all to one person.

05:45.679 --> 05:46.726
This guy!

05:47.180 --> 05:48.352
Oh! (CHUCKLES)

05:48.557 --> 05:49.774
Yeah, you too, you little gremlin.

05:49.975 --> 05:50.976
Now you kids wash up.

05:51.226 --> 05:53.854
We got another long day
of fleecing rubes tomorrow. Go! Go!

05:54.062 --> 05:55.564
(SIGHS) Kids.

05:56.189 --> 06:00.660
<i>Well, Duck-tective, it seems you've
really quacked the case.</i>

06:00.902 --> 06:02.370
(QUACKING)

06:02.779 --> 06:03.780
(LAUGHS)

06:04.698 --> 06:07.247
Stupid duck.
Well, I'm gonna use the john.

06:07.742 --> 06:08.743
You need anything?

06:09.619 --> 06:10.620
(LAUGHS)

06:10.871 --> 06:13.374
I love this guy! Don't you go nowhere.

06:14.457 --> 06:15.424
(WOLF HOWLS DISTANTLY)

06:16.668 --> 06:17.794
(wmo WHISTLES)

06:22.382 --> 06:23.975
Dipper, you wanna do
a toothbrush race?

06:24.175 --> 06:27.930
- Okay.
- STAN: No, no, no!

06:28.680 --> 06:31.809
Wax Stan, he's been murdered!

06:32.017 --> 06:33.189
(GRANDFATHER CLOCK CHIMES)

06:33.685 --> 06:34.652
(CHIMES)

06:35.228 --> 06:36.195
(CHIMES)

06:36.897 --> 06:37.864
(SWOONS)

06:38.231 --> 06:39.323
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

06:42.319 --> 06:43.696
I get up to use the john, right?

06:43.904 --> 06:46.783
And when I come back, blammo!
He's headless!

06:47.157 --> 06:50.161
My expert handcrafting, besmirched.

06:50.368 --> 06:52.416
Besmirched!

06:52.621 --> 06:53.998
Who would do something like this?

06:54.289 --> 06:56.087
What's your opinion, Sheriff Blubs?

06:56.583 --> 06:59.712
Look, we'd love to help you folks,
but let's face the facts.

06:59.920 --> 07:02.048
This case is unsolvable.

07:02.255 --> 07:03.131
- What?
- What?

07:03.340 --> 07:04.933
You take that back, Sheriff Blubs!

07:05.133 --> 07:07.682
You're kidding, right?
There must be evidence, motives.

07:07.844 --> 07:09.061
You know, I could help, if you want.

07:09.262 --> 07:12.732
He's really good. He figured out
who was eating our tin cans!

07:12.974 --> 07:14.817
All signs pointed to the goat.

07:15.018 --> 07:18.192
Yeah, yeah, let the boy help.
He's got a little brain up in his head.

07:18.480 --> 07:20.528
Whoo! Would you look
at what we got here!

07:20.774 --> 07:23.072
City Boy thinks
he's gonna solve a mystery

07:23.276 --> 07:25.745
with his fancy computer phone.

07:25.946 --> 07:28.620
City Boy! City Boy!

07:28.823 --> 07:30.541
You are adorable!

07:30.742 --> 07:32.415
- Adorable?
-(BOTH LAUGH)

07:33.161 --> 07:34.413
He's adorable!

07:34.704 --> 07:38.379
Look, PJs, how about you
leave the investigating to the grownups,

07:38.583 --> 07:39.505
okay?

07:39.709 --> 07:41.177
<i>MAN ON RADIO:
Attention all units. Steve is going to fit</i>

07:41.378 --> 07:42.800
<i>an entire cantaloupe in his mouth.</i>

07:42.963 --> 07:44.260
<i>Repeat, an entire cantaloupe.</i>

07:44.464 --> 07:45.761
It's a 23-16!

07:45.924 --> 07:46.800
Let's move.

07:47.008 --> 07:48.134
(BOTH LAUGHING)

07:48.635 --> 07:51.639
That's it! Mabel, you and me are going to
find the jerk who did this

07:51.805 --> 07:53.022
and get back that head!

07:53.223 --> 07:55.476
Then we'll see who's adorable.

07:56.017 --> 07:56.939
(SNEEZES)

07:57.143 --> 07:59.271
Aww! You sneeze like a kitten.

08:01.022 --> 08:04.196
Wax Stan has lost his head,
and it's up to us to find it.

08:06.611 --> 08:09.239
There were a lot of unhappy customers
at the unveiling.

08:09.447 --> 08:11.541
The murderer could have been anyone!

08:12.033 --> 08:13.831
Gasp! Even us!

08:14.119 --> 08:15.996
In this town, anything is possible.

08:16.162 --> 08:19.257
Ghosts, zombies... Could be months
before we find our first clue.

08:19.457 --> 08:20.959
Hey, look! A clue!

08:21.543 --> 08:23.420
DIPPER: Footprints in the shag carpet.

08:23.628 --> 08:26.097
MABEL: That's weird.
They've got a hole in them.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.091
And they're leading to...

08:28.299 --> 08:29.221
(BOTH GASP)

08:31.636 --> 08:32.761
So what do you think?

08:32.971 --> 08:34.972
In my opinion? This is an ax.

08:35.265 --> 08:38.188
Wait a minute. The lumberjack!

08:38.434 --> 08:39.482
- Of course!
- Of course!

08:39.852 --> 08:41.105
In your face!

08:41.479 --> 08:44.107
He was furious
when he didn't get that free pizza.

08:44.315 --> 08:47.034
Furious enough for murder!

08:47.235 --> 08:48.236
You mean Manly Dan?

08:48.403 --> 08:50.997
Yeah, he hangs out at this crazy
intense biker joint downtown.

08:51.197 --> 08:52.870
Then that's where we're going.

08:53.074 --> 08:55.793
Dude, this is awesome.
You two are, like, the Mystery Twins.

08:56.036 --> 08:57.003
Don't call us that.

08:59.080 --> 09:00.047
(GRUNTS)

09:00.248 --> 09:02.091
Hey, give me
a hand with this coffin, will you?

09:02.459 --> 09:04.507
I'm doing a memorial service
for Wax Stan.

09:04.711 --> 09:06.509
Something small but classy.

09:08.214 --> 09:10.637
Sorry, Grunkle Stan,
but we've got a big break in the case.

09:10.800 --> 09:11.722
Break in the case!

09:11.926 --> 09:14.850
We're heading into town
right now to interrogate the murderer.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.524
We have an ax!
(MIMICS HORROR MOVIE MUSIC)

09:17.682 --> 09:18.854
That seems like the kind of thing

09:19.059 --> 09:20.857
a responsible parent
wouldn't want you doing.

09:21.519 --> 09:24.238
Good thing I'm an uncle.
Avenge me, kids!

09:24.439 --> 09:26.737
Avenge me!

09:33.656 --> 09:35.203
This is the place.

09:36.493 --> 09:37.460
(GASPS)

09:37.660 --> 09:39.287
Got the fake IDs?

09:40.205 --> 09:41.923
Here goes nothing.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.381
Sorry, but we don't serve miners.

09:45.919 --> 09:47.967
Dag-nabbit!

09:49.756 --> 09:51.599
We're here to
interrogate Manly Dan the lumberjack

09:51.800 --> 09:52.972
for the murder of Wax Stan.

09:53.426 --> 09:54.473
Deedle-eedle-eet.

09:55.845 --> 09:56.812
Works for me.

09:57.055 --> 09:58.557
MAN 1: Hey, get out of here!
MAN 2: Hey, come here, you!

09:58.723 --> 10:00.350
-(PEOPLE YELLING)
- He hit me!

10:01.142 --> 10:02.268
(GLASS BREAKING)

10:03.895 --> 10:04.862
(FIGHTING NOISES)

10:05.063 --> 10:05.985
MAN 3: My leg! Please!

10:09.526 --> 10:10.698
He's resting.

10:10.902 --> 10:13.121
All right, let's just try to blend in, okay?

10:13.279 --> 10:14.872
You got it, Dippingsauce!

10:15.824 --> 10:18.168
Hey there, fellow restaurant patron!

10:18.368 --> 10:19.244
Bap!

10:19.452 --> 10:20.874
(GROWLS)

10:21.746 --> 10:22.963
(GRUNTING)

10:23.873 --> 10:26.251
Manly Dan! Just the guy I wanted to see.

10:26.459 --> 10:27.460
Where were you last night?

10:27.669 --> 10:28.886
Punchin' the clock.

10:29.045 --> 10:31.924
- You were at work?
- No, I was punching that clock!

10:32.882 --> 10:35.556
10 p.m., the time of the murder.

10:35.760 --> 10:38.354
So, I guess you've
never seen this before?

10:38.721 --> 10:40.598
- Listen, little girl...
- Actually, I'm...

10:40.765 --> 10:43.814
I wouldn't pick my teeth with that ax.
It's left-handed.

10:44.018 --> 10:47.318
I only use my right hand.
The manly hand!

10:47.897 --> 10:50.776
Get him, get him! (GIGGLES)

10:51.484 --> 10:53.407
Left-handed.

10:53.653 --> 10:56.202
Three, four, five, six.

10:56.364 --> 10:59.288
Oh! Your wife is gonna be beautiful!

10:59.492 --> 11:00.459
Yes!

11:00.660 --> 11:02.788
Mabel, big break in the case.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.790
But will she love me?

11:05.039 --> 11:06.461
It's a left-handed ax.

11:06.666 --> 11:09.545
These are all our suspects.
Manly Dan is right-handed.

11:10.044 --> 11:12.467
That means all we gotta do
is find our left-handed suspect,

11:12.672 --> 11:13.798
and we've got our killer!

11:14.007 --> 11:16.931
Oh, man! We are on fire today!

11:17.135 --> 11:18.603
(IMITATES LASER BLASTS)

11:18.803 --> 11:20.555
Let's find that murderer!

11:38.198 --> 11:39.165
(VVHISTLES)

11:52.420 --> 11:55.424
(GASPS) Mabel!
There's only one person left on this list.

11:55.632 --> 11:57.509
Of course! It all adds up!

11:57.842 --> 11:58.968
(SIREN WAILING)

12:01.554 --> 12:02.976
You kids better be right about this,

12:03.181 --> 12:04.649
or you'll never hear the end of it.

12:04.849 --> 12:06.692
The evidence is irrefutable.

12:06.893 --> 12:08.486
It's so irrefutable.

12:08.645 --> 12:10.613
I'm gonna get to use my nightstick!

12:10.813 --> 12:12.110
You ready? You ready, little fella'?

12:12.357 --> 12:13.574
1w““383i '$222:

12:14.234 --> 12:16.328
On three. One, two...

12:17.028 --> 12:18.200
Nobody move! This is a raid!

12:19.155 --> 12:21.123
What is this? Some kind of raid?

12:22.867 --> 12:25.165
Toby Determined,
you're under arrest for the murder

12:25.370 --> 12:27.338
of the wax body of Grunkle Stan!

12:27.538 --> 12:29.666
You have the right to remain impressed

12:29.874 --> 12:32.047
with our awesome detective work.

12:32.543 --> 12:35.467
Gobbling goose feathers!
I don't understand!

12:35.713 --> 12:37.215
Then allow me to explain.

12:37.507 --> 12:39.885
<i>You were hoping
that Grunkle Stan's new attraction</i>

12:40.093 --> 12:43.267
<i>would be the story that saved
your failing newspaper.</i>

12:43.554 --> 12:44.646
<i>But when the show was a flop,</i>

12:44.847 --> 12:47.521
<i>you decided to go out
and make your own headline.</i>

12:49.018 --> 12:50.144
But you were sloppy!

12:50.353 --> 12:52.731
<i>And all the clues pointed
to a shabby-shoed reporter</i>

12:52.939 --> 12:54.737
<i>who was caught left-handed.</i>

12:54.941 --> 12:57.865
Toby Determined,
you're yesterday's news.

12:58.861 --> 13:04.243
Boy, your little knees must be sore
from jumping to conclusions!

13:04.450 --> 13:05.542
Ha-cha-cha!

13:05.743 --> 13:07.745
I had nothing to do with that murder.

13:07.954 --> 13:09.797
I knew it!
Wait, what did you say? Nothing?

13:09.998 --> 13:11.124
- He said nothing.
- What? Could you repeat...

13:11.332 --> 13:13.585
Then where were you
the night of the break-in?

13:13.835 --> 13:14.802
Um...

13:16.796 --> 13:18.514
<i>Finally, we can be alone,</i>

13:18.715 --> 13:22.845
<i>cardboard cut-out of female news
reporter, Shandra Jimenez!</i>

13:23.428 --> 13:24.395
(SMOOCHES)

13:25.013 --> 13:26.230
- Ew!
- Yuck!

13:26.597 --> 13:27.849
Time-stamp confirms it.

13:28.057 --> 13:30.651
Toby, you're off the hook,
you freak of nature.

13:30.852 --> 13:31.774
Hurray!

13:31.978 --> 13:34.731
But it has to be him!
Check the ax for fingerprints!

13:36.107 --> 13:37.324
No prints at all.

13:37.817 --> 13:38.818
No prints?

13:39.027 --> 13:40.654
I got a headline for you.

13:40.862 --> 13:43.206
"City kids waste everyone's time!"

13:43.406 --> 13:44.953
(LAUGHING)

13:46.701 --> 13:50.581
Boy, I'd be pretty embarrassed
if I was you two!

13:57.211 --> 14:01.762
Kids, Soos, lifeless wax figures,
thank you all for coming.

14:01.966 --> 14:02.933
(BLOWS NOSE)

14:03.343 --> 14:04.845
Some people might say it's wrong

14:05.053 --> 14:07.351
for a man to love
a wax replica of himself.

14:07.555 --> 14:08.431
They're wrong!

14:08.639 --> 14:09.561
Easy, Soos.

14:09.724 --> 14:13.228
Wax Stan, I hope you're
picking pockets in wax heaven.

14:13.811 --> 14:16.189
I'm sorry, I've got glitter in my eye!

14:16.397 --> 14:18.070
(sesame) Dude!

14:18.274 --> 14:20.322
(SIGHS) Those cops
were right about me.

14:20.651 --> 14:23.996
Dipper, we've come so far.
We can't give up now!

14:24.614 --> 14:29.165
But I considered everything,
the weapon, the motive, the clues...

14:29.452 --> 14:30.419
(SIGHS)

14:31.037 --> 14:33.460
Wax Stan's shoe has a hole in it.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.007
All the wax guys have that.

14:35.208 --> 14:38.303
It's where the pole-thingy
attaches to their stand-dealies.

14:38.795 --> 14:43.016
Wait a minute! What has holes
in its shoes and no fingerprints?

14:43.341 --> 14:45.343
Mabel! The murderers are...

14:45.551 --> 14:48.100
Standing right behind you?

14:51.140 --> 14:55.361
Wax Sherlock Holmes!
Wax Shakespeare! Wax Coolio?

14:55.520 --> 14:56.442
Wassup, Holmes?

14:57.772 --> 14:58.989
Oh, my gosh, oh, my gosh.

14:59.774 --> 15:02.618
Congratulations,
my two amateur sleuths.

15:02.819 --> 15:07.290
You've unburied the truth.
And now we're going to bury you!

15:11.202 --> 15:16.208
Bravo, Dipper Pines!
You've discovered our little secret.

15:16.416 --> 15:20.387
Applaud, everyone!
Applaud sarcastically.

15:20.586 --> 15:24.090
No, that sounds too sincere.
Slow clap. There we go.

15:24.298 --> 15:25.470
Nice and condescending.

15:25.675 --> 15:28.178
But how is this possible?
You're made of wax!

15:28.386 --> 15:30.354
Are you magic?

15:30.555 --> 15:34.355
Are we magic?
She wants to know if we're magic.

15:35.351 --> 15:36.443
We're cursed!

15:36.602 --> 15:38.525
Cursed! Cursed!

15:38.729 --> 15:41.903
Cursed to come to life
whenever the moon is waxing!

15:42.108 --> 15:46.079
Your uncle bought us
many years ago at a garage sale.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.202
A haunted garage sale, son!

15:51.325 --> 15:54.499
I must warn you,
these statues come at a terrible price.

15:54.745 --> 15:55.712
Twenty dollars?

15:55.913 --> 15:57.210
I'll just take 'em when you're not looking.

15:57.415 --> 15:59.292
- What?
- I said I was gonna rob you.

15:59.542 --> 16:03.217
<i>SHERLOCK: And so the Mystery Shack
wax collection was born.</i>

16:03.421 --> 16:06.174
<i>By day, we would be
the playthings of man.</i>

16:06.466 --> 16:09.310
COOLIO: <i>But when your uncle went
to sleep, we would rule the night!</i>

16:09.510 --> 16:11.604
- Hey, I told you to stop that.
- Make me!

16:13.222 --> 16:14.189
(LAUGHING)

16:14.599 --> 16:15.566
Huh?

16:17.560 --> 16:20.313
<i>SHERLOCK: It was a charmed life
for us cursed beings.</i>

16:23.399 --> 16:26.824
<i>That is, until your uncle closed up shop.</i>

16:40.458 --> 16:44.964
<i>We've been waiting ten years to get our
revenge on Stan for locking us away.</i>

16:48.674 --> 16:50.722
<i>But we got the wrong guy.</i>

16:50.927 --> 16:52.770
(STAN COUGHING, SPITTING)

16:53.638 --> 16:56.858
So you were trying to murder
Grunkle Stan for real?

16:57.058 --> 17:00.562
You were right all along, Dipper.
Wax people are creepy!

17:00.853 --> 17:01.820
Enough!

17:02.021 --> 17:05.945
Now that you know our secret,
you must die!

17:06.150 --> 17:07.117
(ALL GROWLING)

17:09.987 --> 17:11.364
What do we do? What do we do?

17:11.571 --> 17:12.618
I don't know...

17:17.118 --> 17:18.165
(SCREAMS)

17:19.454 --> 17:22.925
That's it! We can melt them with hotty,
melty things!

17:24.919 --> 17:27.342
Anyone move,
and we'll melt you into candles!

17:27.547 --> 17:28.890
Decorative candles!

17:29.090 --> 17:32.344
You really think you can defeat us?

17:32.552 --> 17:34.520
- I don't know. I'm not really sure.
- It's worth a shot I guess.

17:34.679 --> 17:36.807
So be it. Attack!

17:38.015 --> 17:39.141
Aaah!

17:40.309 --> 17:41.561
Uhh! Aaah!

17:42.603 --> 17:43.570
(GRUNTS)

17:46.399 --> 17:48.618
Interview this, Larry King!

17:48.818 --> 17:51.037
My neck! My beautiful neck!

17:51.237 --> 17:53.331
- Aah!
- Joke's on you, Groucho!

17:53.531 --> 17:55.659
I've heard about a cutting remark,
but this is ridiculous!

17:55.866 --> 17:57.493
Why is there nothing in my hand?

17:58.244 --> 17:59.416
(ROARING)

18:01.956 --> 18:05.586
Ha! Genghis Khan,
you fell harder than the...

18:05.960 --> 18:09.089
I don't know, Jin Dynasty?
Yeah. All right.

18:10.881 --> 18:12.053
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

18:13.009 --> 18:13.976
What's up with that?

18:14.176 --> 18:15.519
Dipper, watch out!

18:17.722 --> 18:19.850
All right, let's get this taken care of.

18:22.685 --> 18:23.732
Catch!

18:30.610 --> 18:31.532
Uh... Uh...

18:31.736 --> 18:33.864
Once your family is out of the way,

18:34.071 --> 18:36.199
we'll rule the night once again!

18:37.825 --> 18:39.623
Don't count on it!

18:40.786 --> 18:42.754
Come back here, you brat!

18:52.590 --> 18:54.763
You really think you can outwit me, boy?

18:55.009 --> 18:59.480
I'm Sherlock bleeding Holmes!
Have you seen my magnifying glass?

18:59.680 --> 19:00.852
It's enormous!

19:01.807 --> 19:03.059
(EXCLAIMING)

19:10.566 --> 19:11.533
(SIGH OF RELIEF)

19:13.611 --> 19:15.705
Any last words?

19:16.030 --> 19:16.997
Um...

19:17.365 --> 19:18.708
You got any sunscreen?

19:18.908 --> 19:20.455
Got any... What?

19:21.452 --> 19:22.578
(GASPS)

19:23.663 --> 19:26.212
- No.
- You know, letting me lead you outside,

19:26.415 --> 19:27.883
probably not your sharpest decision.

19:28.042 --> 19:30.921
Outsmarted by a child in short pants?

19:31.128 --> 19:33.176
[[511

19:33.422 --> 19:35.675
Fiddlesticks! Humbugs!

19:35.966 --> 19:39.641
It's a total kerfuffle! What a hullabaloo...

19:40.012 --> 19:41.605
Case closed!

19:42.723 --> 19:44.396
(SNEEZES)
(SHERLOCK LAUGHS)

19:45.017 --> 19:46.439
You sneeze like a kitten.

19:46.602 --> 19:51.574
Those policemen were right,
you're adorable. Adorable!

19:52.316 --> 19:53.363
Ew.

19:53.859 --> 19:58.660
Though our group be cleft in twain,
man of wax shall rise again!

19:58.864 --> 20:00.832
- You know any limericks?
- Uh...

20:01.283 --> 20:03.832
There once was a dude from Kentucky...

20:04.036 --> 20:04.958
"N°De!
_Aah!

20:05.204 --> 20:06.751
Dipper! You're okay!

20:06.956 --> 20:09.050
You solved the mystery after all.

20:09.250 --> 20:11.298
I couldn't have done it
without my sidekick.

20:11.502 --> 20:13.755
No offense, Dipper,
but you're the sidekick.

20:13.921 --> 20:16.174
What? Says who? Are people
saying that? Have you heard that?

20:16.716 --> 20:19.970
Hot Belgian waffles!
What happened to my parlor?

20:20.970 --> 20:22.597
Your wax figures turned out to be evil,

20:22.763 --> 20:24.390
so we fought them to the death!

20:24.598 --> 20:25.850
I decapitated Larry King.

20:26.475 --> 20:29.228
(LAUGHS) You kids
and your imaginations.

20:29.437 --> 20:31.690
On the bright side, though,
look what we found.

20:32.356 --> 20:35.360
My head! I missed this guy!

20:35.568 --> 20:36.569
You done good, kids!

20:36.819 --> 20:38.947
All right, line up
for some affectionate noogy-ing!

20:39.155 --> 20:40.247
I'm not so sure about that.

20:40.448 --> 20:41.916
Is there any other alternative?

20:42.116 --> 20:43.038
(LAUGHS)

20:43.284 --> 20:44.206
Noogie, noogie, noogie.

20:44.410 --> 20:45.582
(POLICE SIREN APPROACHES)

20:46.328 --> 20:47.545
Solved the case yet, boy?

20:47.747 --> 20:49.966
I'm so confident you're gonna say "no,"

20:50.124 --> 20:53.503
that I'm gonna take a long,
slow sip from my cup of coffee.

20:53.711 --> 20:55.839
(SLURPING)

20:56.046 --> 20:57.263
Actually, the answer is yes!

20:57.465 --> 20:58.432
(SPUTTERS)

20:59.008 --> 20:59.975
(SCREAMS)

21:00.593 --> 21:01.685
(SCREAMS)

21:01.886 --> 21:02.853
(SCREAMS)

21:03.679 --> 21:05.522
- It burns! It burns!
- My eyes! Drive! Drive!

21:06.348 --> 21:07.395
(ALL LAUGHING)

21:08.768 --> 21:10.611
- They got scalded!
-(CAR CRASHES)

21:11.020 --> 21:13.273
So, did you get rid of
all of the wax figures?

21:13.439 --> 21:15.862
I am 99% sure that I did!

21:16.066 --> 21:17.318
Good enough for me!

21:21.155 --> 21:23.704
(LAUGHING)

21:23.908 --> 21:24.830
Huh?

21:25.034 --> 21:27.332
So, you're a rat. Tell me about that.

21:27.620 --> 21:29.167
Hey, get back here!

21:30.122 --> 21:31.169
I'm hopping!

21:31.373 --> 21:34.627
<i>I'm hopping after a rat that stole my ear.</i>

21:35.419 --> 21:36.341
Hmm.

21:36.545 --> 21:38.468
Hey, Dipper, what do you think is better?

21:38.672 --> 21:41.266
Sequins, or llama hair?

21:41.759 --> 21:46.390
The llama hair.
Llamas are nature's greatest warriors.

21:48.682 --> 21:49.774
Thanks, Dipper!
